OL,3,CIs Reeves to blame for looming income
OL,4,Ctax rises?
OL,6,FWhere she and the Treasury are at
OL,7,Ffault, however, is that she should
OL,8,Fhave pre-empted the downgrade as soon
OL,9,Fas she came into government, and
OL,10,Fcertainly at the last budget, because
OL,11,Fthe OBR's excessive optimism was
OL,12,Fobvious and widely discussed.
OL,14,FIn other words, as she herself
OL,15,Fconceded, there is nothing new about
OL,16,Fthe UK's most serious economic
OL,17,Ffrailty, that the amount of income
OL,18,Fgenerated by each of us on average
OL,19,Ffrom our stock of capital is growing
OL,20,Ftoo slowly to support any meaningful
OL,21,Frise in living standards.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
